A vintage 1960s corporate illustration style image showing a large wall-mounted calendar grid in warm cream and burnt orange tones, with multiple translucent calendar layers floating and overlapping in front of it like acetate sheets. Small stylized figures in mid-century business attire stand on different calendar layers, placing colorful flag pins and geometric markers on various dates. The calendars cascade at different angles, creating depth and dimension. Warm amber lighting streams through office windows with venetian blinds casting striped shadows. The scene has a nostalgic advertising poster quality with muted mustard yellows, avocado greens, and rust browns typical of the era.
